# SECURITY HEADERS PATTERNS

## Content Security Policy (CSP) Configuration

### ✅ Complete CSP for Firebase + reCAPTCHA

When using Firebase Authentication with Google reCAPTCHA, your CSP **MUST** include:

```javascript
const csp = [
  "default-src 'self'",
  "script-src 'self' 'unsafe-eval' 'unsafe-inline' https://www.gstatic.com https://www.google.com",
  "style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com",
  "img-src 'self' data: https: blob:",
  "font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com",
  // CRITICAL: Must include google.com and gstatic.com for reCAPTCHA
  "connect-src 'self' https://*.firebaseio.com https://*.googleapis.com https://firestore.googleapis.com wss://*.firebaseio.com https://www.google.com https://www.gstatic.com",
  "frame-src 'self' https://www.google.com",
  "object-src 'none'",
  "base-uri 'self'",
  "form-action 'self'",
  "frame-ancestors 'self'",
].join('; ');
```

### ⚠️ Common CSP Pitfalls

1. **Missing reCAPTCHA Domains**
   - **Error**: `Content Security Policy directive: "connect-src"` blocking `www.google.com/recaptcha/api2/clr`
   - **Fix**: Add `https://www.google.com https://www.gstatic.com` to `connect-src`

2. **Firebase Real-time Database**
   - Requires: `wss://*.firebaseio.com` for WebSocket connections
   - Requires: `https://*.firebaseio.com` for REST API

3. **Firestore**
   - Requires: `https://firestore.googleapis.com`
   - Requires: `https://*.googleapis.com` (for auth tokens)

### 🔍 Debugging CSP Issues

**Symptoms:**
- Login fails silently
- reCAPTCHA doesn't load
- Firebase connections timeout

**Check browser console for:**
```
[ERROR] Fetch API cannot load https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api2/clr?k=...
Refused to connect because it violates the document's Content Security Policy.
```

**Solution:** Add the blocked domain to the appropriate CSP directive.

