## Testing CSP Changes

1. **Open DevTools Console** (F12)
2. **Filter for "Content Security Policy"**
3. **Look for blocked resources**
4. **Add allowed domains to CSP**
5. **Test in production** (CSP violations may only appear in prod)

---

## Third-Party Service CSP Requirements

| Service | Required CSP Directives |
|---------|------------------------|
| **Google reCAPTCHA** | `script-src: https://www.gstatic.com https://www.google.com`<br>`connect-src: https://www.google.com https://www.gstatic.com`<br>`frame-src: https://www.google.com` |
| **Firebase Auth** | `connect-src: https://*.googleapis.com` |
| **Firestore** | `connect-src: https://firestore.googleapis.com https://*.googleapis.com` |
| **Firebase Storage** | `img-src: https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com`<br>`connect-src: https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com` |
| **Google Fonts** | `style-src: https://fonts.googleapis.com`<br>`font-src: https://fonts.gstatic.com` |

---

## Security Checklist

- [ ] CSP includes all Firebase domains
- [ ] reCAPTCHA domains added if using Firebase Auth with email/password
- [ ] Test login in production (not just localhost)
- [ ] Check browser console for CSP violations
- [ ] Verify WebSocket connections work (real-time listeners)
